Goals of the course: 

Learn the basics of Industrial Automation
Levels and components in a system 
Programing Languages:
- Ladder Logic 
- Function block diagrams
OPC SCADA


Industrial Automation concept - the use of set technologies and automatic control devices for control systems


Indutrial Automation Components:

PLC - programming logic controllers
DCS - distributed control systems 
Field industrial devices 
Industrial comunication and networking
HMI - Human-machine interface 
SCADA - Supervisory control and data acquisition

Levels in Industrial Automation: 
- Field level

- Control Level

- Application/Managment Level


Industrial Network: 

DeviceNet 
Modbus 
HART Comunication Protocol
PROFIBUS 
Ethernet 









